main event: A civilian observer reported seeing two objects in the sky during the evening hours on 11 November 1963.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 15 minutes., The objects were reported as having varied courses., A news article was submitted by a Congressman requesting further investigation into the sighting., There were subsequent observations of a helicopter in the area that were consistent with local newspaper reports., The conclusions of the investigation indicated the sighting could possibly be a balloon or unknown aircraft.
